The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Tobacco ad ban 
                                                                                                               Tobacco ad ban 
                            
	New Delhi, March 18: The government has barred tobacco companies from sponsoring sports events and awards programmes, reports our special correspondent.         
	The information and broadcasting ministry has issued a notification banning such sponsorships, saying the tobacco firms are engaging in brand extension         
	No depiction, direct or indirect reference promoting the prohibited product will be allowed, an official said.        
	India is the second-largest consumer of tobacco.                                                                                                                                                                           
